               <p>TIMOTHY COLEMAN JOHNSON. I am a <rs id="t18240715-109-viclabel584" type="occupation">builder</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240715-109-victim994 t18240715-109-viclabel584"></join> - I was building two houses in <placeName id="t18240715-109-crimeloc585">Hare-street-fields, Bethnal-green</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18240715-109-crimeloc585" type="placeName" value="Hare-street-fields, Bethnal-green"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18240715-109-crimeloc585" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240715-109-off582 t18240715-109-crimeloc585"></join>; and left the articles stated in the indictment in one house on the 25th of June - I fastened it with a padlock - I went there again about eleven o'clock in the morning, and and found the padlock wrenched off, and the property gone. On the 1st of July, I was passing an iron stall in Spitalfields, and saw them exposed for sale - the woman described a man to me. I fetched an officer, and while we were there the prisoner came up; the woman said he was the man, and the officer took him.</p>
               <p>CATHERINE CONDE. I live in French-alley, Spitalfields. On the 26th of June, the prisoner sold me two thumb latches, two turn buckles, five or six buttons, and some brass nails. He came to the door while I was talking to the officer and was taken.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240715-109-person995">
                  CHARLES 
                  STILL
               <interp inst="t18240715-109-person995" type="surname" value="STILL"></interp>
